{
  "stem": "13690.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were wearing some kind of a uniform.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that they belonged to a certain extreme organization which were the anti-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I would not say 'anti-Semitism.' They were anti-Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I did not understand the full meaning of the word 'anti-Semitism.'",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We did-- always, my father-- my late father was always speaking about the danger, obviously since the time of Hitler coming to power.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And being that our town was so close to the German border, we were always worried about it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But this was not the question that we were aware.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were aware.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But still and all, not every house had a radio.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not every house had a telephone.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, in turn, we were limited even with the newspapers, so to say.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Even though that the government of Poland, as I read, later years, between 1920 and 1939, it was most of the time was not a free country.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was a dictatorship under the Polish government, where no actual publications or papers could be printed that their own way of thinking.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Besides, I would say people had-- even if they were aware of anti-Semitism, there was no way where to run.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From later time that I was told, a later date, that to Palestine you could only go if you were either belonging to an organization that's one of the scouts organization, or from the extreme left of the halutzim, which means 'the pioneers.' Or the ones, let's say, like my father, having a family-- he could have also emigrated by showing that he has means to live in Israel.",
      "word_count": 69
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, a certain amount of money, which will give him the preference of going to Israel and settling, cultivate the land of Israel.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At those days, of course, not Israel-- it was Palestine.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
